SAKHILE NDLAZI Despite the ongoing nationwide bus strike, some commuters forged forward and queued at the Pretoria Station today. Although not packed as usual, the bus station was somewhat still operation, especially for commuters travelling outside the country. Tinashe Nandoro, who was travelling to, Harare, Zimbabwe  said he bought his ticket last week because he had a traditional family ceremony to urgently attend. “I couldn’t  just sit back and wait, so I took a chance this morning despite the national bus strike, and it seems I’m in luck,” he said. A handful of bus drivers were protesting a stones throw away from the the buses. They pointed and hurled insults at other bus drivers when they drove past calling them “sellouts”. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
